[2
Date: Tue, 24 Jul 2001 15:34:58 -0400
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Australian Broadcasting Company, Wed 25 Jul 2001 [edited
<http://www.abc.net.au/ra/newsdaily/s334757.htm>

Dengue fever epidemic claims 38 lives in Vietnam
------------------------------------------------
An epidemic of the mosquito-borne dengue fever has claimed the lives
of 38 people in Vietnam since the start of the year [2001 and left
more than 14 000 others sick. The AFP news agency quotes a health
ministry official as saying that the number of dengue cases represents
a 74 percent increase over the same period of last year. The official
says the number of cases is still increasing in several Vietnamese
provinces. The outbreak is particularly [serious in the Mekong Delta
region and the central province
of Ha Tinh, where moist and humid conditions provide ideal breeding
grounds for mosquitoes.
